sequenceDiagram
    participant Deploy as deploy.sh Container
    participant K8sAPI as OpenShift API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant ODHOp as ODH Operator<br/>(KfDef Controller)
    participant Manifests as odh-manifests<br/>(tarball file://)
    participant Prom as Prometheus<br/>9090/TCP
    participant BB as Blackbox Exporter<br/>9114/TCP HTTPS
    participant AM as Alertmanager<br/>9093/TCP
    participant ClusterProm as Cluster Prometheus<br/>9091/TCP HTTPS
    participant Components as Platform Components<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant Endpoints as User-Facing Endpoints<br/>HTTPS
    participant PD as PagerDuty<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant DMS as Dead Man's Snitch<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant SMTP as SMTP Server<br/>STARTTLS

    Note over Deploy,K8sAPI: Flow 1: Platform Deployment
    Deploy->>K8sAPI: Create namespaces<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token<br/>TLS 1.2+
    Deploy->>K8sAPI: Apply KfDef CRs<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>ODHOp: KfDef watch event
    ODHOp->>Manifests: Load manifests<br/>file:// protocol
    Manifests-->>ODHOp: YAML manifests
    ODHOp->>K8sAPI: Create component Deployments<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token<br/>TLS 1.2+
    Deploy->>K8sAPI: Apply monitoring stack<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    Deploy->>K8sAPI: Apply network policies<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    Deploy->>K8sAPI: Install dashboard config + ISV tiles<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token

    Note over Prom,Components: Flow 2: Prometheus Metrics Federation
    Prom->>ClusterProm: Federate metrics<br/>9091/TCP HTTPS<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (SA)<br/>TLS (service CA)
    Prom->>Components: Scrape component metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP<br/>Auth: None
    Prom->>BB: Query probe results<br/>9114/TCP HTTPS<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    BB->>Endpoints: Probe availability<br/>HTTPS<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (SA)
    Endpoints-->>BB: HTTP status
    BB-->>Prom: Probe metrics
    Components-->>Prom: /metrics response
    ClusterProm-->>Prom: Federated metrics

    Note over Prom,SMTP: Flow 3: Alert Notification (Managed Service)
    Prom->>AM: Fire alert<br/>9093/TCP HTTP<br/>Loopback, no encryption
    AM->>PD: Critical alerts<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Service Key
    AM->>SMTP: Email notifications<br/>STARTTLS<br/>Auth: Username/Password
    AM->>DMS: Watchdog heartbeat<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: URL Token
